METHODOLOGY 

The project follows a modular development approach. First, the user interface is created using HTML and styled using CSS. JavaScript is then used to implement core functionalities such as login validation, book management, and search operations.

The system stores book data in LocalStorage in JSON format. When the page loads, JavaScript retrieves stored data and displays it dynamically. CRUD operations are implemented to manage books efficiently.

Each action updates LocalStorage instantly, ensuring data persistence. The project is tested in different browsers to ensure reliability.

 
